"<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong>Poisonings</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggfXh-OYQzq_childItem_1","label":"ggfXh-OYQzq_childItem_1","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong>Car accidents</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggfXh-OYQzq_childItem_2","label":"ggfXh-OYQzq_childItem_2","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong>Broken bones</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggfXh-OYQzq_childItem_3","label":"ggfXh-OYQzq_childItem_3","default":"<p><strong>Cancer</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggmsTmV2VWD_text","label":"ggmsTmV2VWD_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong>Max was choking again, and this time I knew he might die.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg1sEMkrRdF_text","label":"gg1sEMkrRdF_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">You name it, I've seen it all.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">I'm talking about </span><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#D31D1D;font-size:16px;\"><strong>GDV - Gastric Dilatation Volvulus</strong></span><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">. Most people call it \"bloat.\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggoKSZEGOPM_text","label":"ggoKSZEGOPM_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">And it kills <strong>30% of dogs</strong> even with immediate emergency surgery.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggGGytvYLbg_text","label":"ggGGytvYLbg_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">And it kills <strong>30% of dogs</strong> even with immediate emergency surgery.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggDzWhreIfS_text","label":"ggDzWhreIfS_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Problem Most Dog Owners Don't Even Know Exists</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggMdeTQ5xsq_text","label":"ggMdeTQ5xsq_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Here's what haunts me: <strong>Every single one of these cases starts the exact same way.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">The owner always says the same thing: \"Doctor, he's always been a fast eater. We thought it was cute how much he loved his food.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">They describe their dog as a \"vacuum cleaner,\" a \"food inhaler,\" someone who \"cleans their bowl in under 60 seconds.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Many of them even <strong>post videos online</strong> of their dog's \"enthusiastic eating style\" that friends find hilarious.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">They have absolutely no idea they're filming a potentially fatal medical condition happening twice daily.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Because here's the terrifying truth: <strong>every meal becomes Russian roulette </strong>with invisible bullets that could explode anywhere from 20 minutes to 2 hours after eating.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">But it wasn't until <strong>Jennifer Thompson rushed into my ER</strong> at 9:47 PM on a Tuesday night that I realized how desperately pet parents needed to know this information.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggskKVJkbpD_text","label":"ggskKVJkbpD_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Tuesday Night That Changed Everything</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg9cl3rc_d4_text","label":"gg9cl3rc_d4_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>The Problem Most Dog Owners Don't Even Know Exists</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggNuNAr9n-Q_text","label":"ggNuNAr9n-Q_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>The Tuesday Night That Changed Everything</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggFkV4tNgXs_text","label":"ggFkV4tNgXs_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">It all started with what seemed like a routine emergency call.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Jennifer burst through my doors carrying Sophie, her 4-year-old Corgi, who was <strong>foaming at the mouth</strong> and couldn't lie down.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">\"She had her normal dinner 20 minutes ago,\" Jennifer sobbed. \"She always eats really fast - finishes in about 60 seconds. We call her our little vacuum cleaner.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">One look at Sophie's <strong>distended, rock-hard stomach</strong> and I knew we had minutes, not hours.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">\"Sophie has GDV. Her stomach has flipped and is cutting off blood supply. We need to operate immediately.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\"><strong>$4,800. Four hours of surgery. One blood transfusion.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggfBH1J7DiM_text","label":"ggfBH1J7DiM_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Sophie survived. Barely.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">At 3 AM, while Sophie recovered, I pulled up her x-rays to show Jennifer what had nearly killed her beloved companion.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggR5ng7c4ZD_text","label":"ggR5ng7c4ZD_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">It all started with what seemed like a routine emergency call.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Jennifer burst through my doors carrying Sophie, her 4-year-old Corgi, who was <strong>foaming at the mouth</strong> and couldn't lie down.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"She had her normal dinner 20 minutes ago,\" Jennifer sobbed. \"She always eats really fast - finishes in about 60 seconds. We call her our little vacuum cleaner.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">One look at Sophie's <strong>distended, rock-hard stomach</strong> and I knew we had minutes, not hours.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Sophie has GDV. Her stomach has flipped and is cutting off blood supply. We need to operate immediately.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>$4,800. Four hours of surgery. One blood transfusion.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg3dUcRPNW1_text","label":"gg3dUcRPNW1_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\"><strong>\"See this dark area? That's all the air she swallowed. Every fast meal creates this bomb in their stomach.\"</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg-BVBRwlib_text","label":"gg-BVBRwlib_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">That's when I realized something that completely changed how I practice emergency veterinary medicine.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggfOfYAj3e5_text","label":"ggfOfYAj3e5_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Sophie survived. Barely.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">At 3 AM, while Sophie recovered, I pulled up her x-rays to show Jennifer what had nearly killed her beloved companion.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>\"See this dark area? That's all the air she swallowed. Every fast meal creates this bomb in their stomach.\"</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggsTlLdz5t7_text","label":"ggsTlLdz5t7_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">That's when I realized something that completely changed how I practice emergency veterinary medicine.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggz3ohdxyPN_text","label":"ggz3ohdxyPN_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>Shocking Truth: The Real Root Cause Nobody Talks About</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggz__7wwX_K_text","label":"ggz__7wwX_K_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Most people think fast eating is just a personality quirk.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>They're dead wrong.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Fast eating triggers something called the <strong>competitive feeding response</strong> - an ancient neurological pathway left over from when dogs lived in packs and had to defend their food from competitors.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Here's how this silent killer works in your kitchen:</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">When your dog sees food presented in any pile formation, their brain <strong>immediately switches into survival mode.</strong> They think: \"I need to consume this resource before competitors arrive.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">This triggers rapid gulping motions designed to inhale maximum food in minimum time.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">But here's the deadly part: This gulping motion forces your dog to<strong> swallow massive amounts of air</strong> along with their food.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggnUH6WkHkN_text","label":"ggnUH6WkHkN_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Think of it like inflating a balloon inside your dog's stomach. <strong>These air bubbles create gas pressure</strong> that can literally flip their stomach upside down.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Once the stomach twists, <strong>blood supply gets cut off</strong>. The stomach tissue begins dying within minutes.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Even worse:</strong> The twisted stomach traps gas inside, creating more pressure that can <strong>rupture the stomach wall </strong>or compress the lungs until your dog can't breathe.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggbGadrwJGz_text","label":"ggbGadrwJGz_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Without immediate surgery, <strong>most dogs die within 30 minutes</strong> of stomach torsion.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">The tragic irony? <strong>Your dog's love for their food is literally killing them.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggNZPMebt7u_text","label":"ggNZPMebt7u_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>Why Every \"Solution\" You've Tried Has Failed</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggEOD5t6IL9_text","label":"ggEOD5t6IL9_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">You've probably tried everything:</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggOoou9kZzV_childItem_0","label":"ggOoou9kZzV_childItem_0","default":"<p><strong>Hand feeding</strong> (exhausting and you can't leave your dog alone)</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggOoou9kZzV_childItem_1","label":"ggOoou9kZzV_childItem_1","default":"<p><strong>Tennis balls in the bowl </strong>(choking hazards that dogs remove anyway)</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggOoou9kZzV_childItem_2","label":"ggOoou9kZzV_childItem_2","default":"<p><strong>Basic slow feeder bowls </strong>(dogs \"beat\" them and still gulp)</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggOoou9kZzV_childItem_3","label":"ggOoou9kZzV_childItem_3","default":"<p>Puzzle toys (too complicated, food gets stuck)</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggcnIHDQCEc_text","label":"ggcnIHDQCEc_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>But we already know that's impossible when</strong> every single solution still presents food as one pile that triggers competitive feeding instincts.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Traditional slow feeders might reduce eating speed by <strong>40%</strong>, but they only reduce air intake by <strong>10%</strong> - and it's the air intake that kills.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggb4CrletVD_text","label":"ggb4CrletVD_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>So What's The Solution?</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggblE_SfVsh_text","label":"ggblE_SfVsh_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Here's a secret not many people know:</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>The problem isn't that your dog eats too fast.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>﻿The problem is that their brain thinks they're fighting for survival every single meal.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">After Sophie's surgery, I spent months researching neurological feeding triggers in dogs. I discovered breakthrough research from the <strong>Journal of Veterinary Behavior </strong>showing that when food presentation is broken up dramatically enough,<strong> the competitive feeding response completely deactivates.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Instead, dogs switch into what researchers call <strong>\"foraging mode\" </strong>- the natural, calm feeding pattern dogs use when they're not under threat.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">This is how dogs are supposed to eat. No gulping. No air swallowing.<strong> No life-threatening gas bubbles</strong>.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">The technology that makes this possible is called </span><span style=\"background-color:#F5C242;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Neurological Reset Technology.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg0__qHhkpD_text","label":"gg0__qHhkpD_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The One Bowl That Actually Saves Lives</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggkloHnyau4_text","label":"ggkloHnyau4_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">The problem was finding this technology in a form that regular dog owners could actually use.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">That's when I partnered with Waggier, a company that's helped <strong>over 50,000 dogs</strong> transition from dangerous gulping to peaceful foraging.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Together, we developed something I now recommend to <strong>every single client: The PaceBowl Honeycomb Slow Feeder Bowl.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggsALIi5J96_text","label":"ggsALIi5J96_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">This isn't just another slow feeder bowl.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">The <strong>PaceBowl's honeycomb maze design</strong> breaks up food presentation so completely that your dog's brain <strong>cannot recognize it as a single resource to defend.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Instead of thinking \"I need to gulp this down before competitors come,\" your dog thinks \"I need to forage through this natural environment.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>The competitive feeding response shuts off entirely.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg6KqIoZwKn_childItem_0","label":"gg6KqIoZwKn_childItem_0","default":"<p>Made from <strong>medical-grade stainless steel</strong> that never harbors bacteria like plastic bowls do.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg6KqIoZwKn_childItem_1","label":"gg6KqIoZwKn_childItem_1","default":"<p>Dishwasher safe for easy cleaning.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg6KqIoZwKn_childItem_2","label":"gg6KqIoZwKn_childItem_2","default":"<p>Veterinarian approved by emergency vets who see GDV cases nightly.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gglBSfWvk8L_text","label":"gglBSfWvk8L_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Most importantly: <strong>It works from the very first meal.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggLXhobKtUA_text","label":"ggLXhobKtUA_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Results Speak For Themselves</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg5Gec1T8iy_text","label":"gg5Gec1T8iy_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">The clinical research is remarkable. In studies of dogs using the <strong>PaceBowl</strong>:</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggUcKIZZ2KJ_childItem_0","label":"ggUcKIZZ2KJ_childItem_0","default":"<p>87% eliminated gulping behavior completely within one meal</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggUcKIZZ2KJ_childItem_1","label":"ggUcKIZZ2KJ_childItem_1","default":"<p>Dishwasher safe for easy cleaning.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggUcKIZZ2KJ_childItem_2","label":"ggUcKIZZ2KJ_childItem_2","default":"<p>Veterinarian approved by emergency vets who see GDV cases nightly.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggI8yIaJFq9_text","label":"ggI8yIaJFq9_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">But what really matters are the real-world results I see in my practice.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Jennifer sent me a video <strong>one week after Sophie's surgery</strong>. Instead of vacuuming her food in 60 seconds, Sophie was calmly foraging through her honeycomb bowl, taking <strong>nearly 8 minutes to finish her meal.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gglsksZrHxz_text","label":"gglsksZrHxz_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Charlotte S. </span><span style=\"color:#BF2424;font-size:14px;\">Verified Review </span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">| Rating: ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️</span><br><strong>\"I can finally breathe again\"</strong><br>\"No more watching her eat in terror. No more Russian roulette twice a day.\"</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggcT5lymE3c_text","label":"ggcT5lymE3c_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Mark C. </span><span style=\"color:#BF2424;font-size:14px;\">Verified Review </span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">| Rating: ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️</span><br><strong>This actually works!</strong><br>\"Our Great Dane Max went from inhaling his food in 45 seconds to peacefully eating for 12 minutes. It's like watching a completely different dog.\"</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggsvTxakhMM_text","label":"ggsvTxakhMM_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Evelyn H. </span><span style=\"color:#BF2424;font-size:14px;\">Verified Review </span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">| Rating: ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️</span><br><strong>\"My dog is so much calmer!\"</strong><br>\"I haven't had a single vomiting episode since we switched to the PaceBowl three months ago. My German Shepherd actually seems happier and more relaxed around meal time.\"</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggNWoIAIZ5z_text","label":"ggNWoIAIZ5z_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">This is what happens when you deactivate the neurological trigger instead of just slowing down eating speed.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggaEa2fD7zm_text","label":"ggaEa2fD7zm_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>How Can You Get Your Hands on a PaceBowl?</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggXDeU66Gjl_text","label":"ggXDeU66Gjl_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Hidden Cost of Waiting</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggLVOhGLa32_text","label":"ggLVOhGLa32_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>...And what's the price?</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Well, the first question is a tricky one...</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Because manufacturing the <strong>Waggier PaceBowl</strong> isn't cheap or easy...</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>The medical-grade stainless steel</strong> costs 8x more than plastic... The precision honeycomb molding requires specialized equipment... Each bowl goes through <strong>17 quality control checks</strong> before shipping...</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">So we are at a constant risk of <strong>running out of stock</strong>.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>We can only produce about 500 units per month </strong>due to the complexity of the stainless steel molding process.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">But I hate to admit that we are currently failing to keep up with demand.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>The need is just too urgent.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Emergency veterinarians who have seen the clinical research are now recommending the PaceBowl to every client with a fast-eating dog.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Not to mention the thousands of dog owners who've experienced the terror of a bloat scare.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">They were desperate when they discovered the bowl that could <strong>eliminate the neurological trigger </strong>causing their dog's dangerous gulping, and I'm sure that many of them are placing their orders right now.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">All this makes our stock run out quickly every time we get a new shipment.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Last month alone, <strong>over 2,000 emergency veterinarians</strong> started recommending the PaceBowl to clients after seeing the clinical research.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>We sold out completely in 8 days.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Now, if you are reading this article, it means that we probably have a few bowls left in stock, otherwise we would've taken the page down.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">But unfortunately, we cannot guarantee for how much longer.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggljIRlXtzZ_text","l